text = "Burpenson Air Force Base. 196X.

Exchange officer Captain Crumpitt is setting at his desk reading a rather unsettling edition of the Davenport Daily, reporting strong rumours that the USSR government has built a doomsday device, capable of wiping out all life of Earth when triggered at a report of a nuclear attack from the enemy.

Just as he throws away the paper in the waste basket, Crumpitt notices a bunch of his fellow troops evacuating the base, carrying radio equipment. When asking around, he learns that the base is put on red alert and that all radios must be confiscated. Orders from General Griffin.

As he grabs his radio from his office’s drawer, he turns it out of curiosity and he hears… music. Jazzy music. Just regular civilian broadcasting."
